items.name: Ring Girl
items.description:
This LoRA makes UFC ring girls.

Canonical results include the term "ring girl" if you're going for that. Otherwise, you might get a girl holding one of these signs in some other context (which can be equally as fun).

Include "holding a sign" to get a big octagon sign indicating the round.

The following will dictate which round:

"rnd1" - Round 1 sign

"rnd2" - Round 2 sign

"rnd3" - Round 3 sign

"rnd4" - Round 4 sign**

"rnd5" - Round 5 sign**

**Note: round 4 and 5 are less reliable, as there were less training images available.

If a round isn't chosen, it can lead to the model thinking the girl in question is a fighter.

"UFC" is another useful keyword.

Example: a photo of a ring girl, holding a sign, UFC, rnd3, best quality, photorealistic, fine details <lora:r1ngg1rl:0.7>

Have fun!

items.name: chibi-character
items.description:
介绍:

  • 最近我创作了一些loha的作品，但我意识到很多人可能不太熟悉正确的使用方法。因此，我使用了相同的训练集来训练了lora模型。

  • 在正向的prompt中仍然使用chibi。

  • 如果有需要，你也可以尝试使用EasyNegative模型来处理一些负面情况。

  • 或许你可以调高你的权重或者降低，训练时我将lora的权重降低，便于你们使用。

  • 我非常欢迎大家提出意见，并希望你们能在评论区分享你们的反馈和创作。非常感谢！

Translation:

  • Recently, I have created some artworks using loha. However, I realized that many people may not be familiar with the correct usage. Therefore, I trained the lora model using the same training dataset.

  • chibi is still used as the prompt for positive creations.

  • If needed, you can also try using the EasyNegative model to handle negative scenarios.

  • Perhaps you can increase or decrease your weight. During training, I will lower the weight of 'lora' to facilitate your usage.

  • I warmly welcome everyone to provide feedback and share your creations in the comments section. Thank you very much!

v1 v2 v3的区别：

  • 训练集：不同版本可能使用不同的训练集来进行模型的训练。训练集的规模、质量和多样性对于模型的性能影响很大，因此不同版本的训练集可能导致性能差异。

  • 超参数的调整：超参数是模型训练过程中需要手动设置的参数，例如学习率、批大小、层数等。不同版本可能对超参数进行了不同的调整，以优化模型性能。

  • 插件的使用：可能不同版本采用了不同的插件或扩展来增强模型的能力。

  • 总结，使用v3就可以了。


The differences between v1, v2, and v3 are as follows:

  • Training Dataset: Different versions may use different training datasets for model training. The size, quality, and diversity of the training dataset have a significant impact on the model's performance, thus leading to performance variations among different versions.

  • Hyperparameter Tuning: Hyperparameters are manually set parameters during the model training process, such as learning rate, batch size, and the number of layers. Different versions may adjust these hyperparameters differently to optimize the model's performance.

  • Plugin Usage: Different versions may incorporate different plugins or extensions to enhance the model's capabilities.

  • In summary, v3 is fine.

items.name: LibrarySpec_图书馆大台阶
items.description:
The model draws great images of big steps where people rest and read, which is a common design in library indoor design. I have found this extremely useful. Use with Realistic_Vision or SD original model, but the former works better. Trigger Word is //readingsteps, also try front (/top/pers) view to produce different angles.

Please rate my model or post your image , I could really use some feedback.

用来画大台阶有奇效，尤其是室内阅览大台阶。基础模型可用 Realistic_Vision 或 SD 本模，不过前者效果较好。触发词是：//readingsteps，使用 front (/top/pers) view 来控制视角。

计划中要做的还有高大阅览空间、书架墙两个功能，这样才能叫 LibrarySpec 嘛。

如果有试用的话，欢迎评分或上传图片，期待网友的反馈。

items.name: LatentByRatio  - ComfyUI JNode SDXL SD1.5 SD2.x
items.description:
To support my work, you could buy me a coffee

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/JasonAICreator

This node is aims to help with different models on different aspect ratio.

I was mainly using SD1.5 and remember a lot of width, height like 512,768 which is pretty annoying. While using SDXL 1024 based model, I don't know what width height should I use to setup the latent space.

Therefore, I created this custom_nodes to create latent space more easier by selecting model and aspect ratio.

Further update might setup a config file for the ratio and let user could give it a custom ratio. But now it is enough to use.

Special thanks to ⛧ Sytan ⛧ on SDXL channel who created the very nice workflow and I based on that to create nodes.

Example:

Installation:

download the zip, unzip and put py files into Comfyui/custom_nodes folder

load the workflow using right panel "load" button.

HameFMixはNSFW画像の生成もできるアニメモデルです。Hassaku,meina,CounterFeitの3モデルを中心にマージをしました。

Adjustは素晴らしい機能ですが、ノイズ強度を上げるとイラストが崩れてしまう欠点がありました。しかし、色々モデルを生成しているうちにCFGScaleFixを使用することで改善できることがわかりました。

このモデルはCFGの値を高く取り、CFGscaleFixを使うことで（特に背景と服装が）超高精細なイラストを生成することができます。CFGScaleFixを使用しない場合は生成画像にノイズが多く残ってしまうため、あまりパッとしないイラストになるでしょう。

CFGScaleFixは以下のように設定すると上手くいきます。（CFGは30~35に設定）

Mimic scale: 7, Threshold percentile: 100, Mimic mode: Sawtooth, Mimic scale minimum: 22~30, CFG mode: Sawtooth, CFG scale minimum: 3, Scheduler value: 20

4つ5つのモデルがありますが、モデル内容自体は全く同じでAdjustの設定が違います。Aを基本として、Bがノイズ強度強め、Cがコントラスト強めに設定しています。そしてEはノイズとコントラストを最大限強化したテストモデルです。

Bはノイズ強度を限界まで高めているため、イラストにちらつきが残ります。私は、それがかっこよく見えたのでノイズ残りをわざと残しましたが、気に入らない人も多いかもしれないです。

そしてDは、CFGScaleFixを使用しなくてもノイズ飛びが少なくなるように調整しました。このモデルはDPM2＋＋ 2MSDEの使用を強く推奨します。

また、Hires.Fixを使用すると描き込みが薄れてしまうので、高解像度イラストを作るときはt2i→i2iの二段生成を推奨します。

English（DeepL translate）

This is a very specific model for the use of CFGScaleFix!

Please read the following text carefully!

HameFMix is an animation model that can also generate NSFW images.

We merged mainly three models: Hassaku, meina, and CounterFeit.

Adjust is a great feature, but it had the drawback that the illustration would collapse when the noise intensity was increased. However, after generating various models, I found that it could be improved by using CFGScaleFix.

Without CFGScaleFix, the generated image will have a lot of noise, and the illustration will not be very crisp.

The CFGScaleFix can be set as follows. (CFG is set to 30~35)

Mimic scale: 7, Threshold percentile: 100, Mimic mode: Sawtooth, Mimic scale minimum: 22~30, CFG mode: Sawtooth, CFG scale minimum: 3, Scheduler value: 20

There are four five models, but the models themselves are exactly the same, with different Adjust settings: A is set as the basic model, B is set for stronger noise intensity, and C is set for stronger contrast. And E is a test model with maximum noise and contrast enhancement.

B is set to the limit of noise intensity, so there is some flicker in the illustration. I intentionally left the noise residue because I thought it looked cool, but many people may not like it.

And D was adjusted to reduce noise jumps without the use of CFGScaleFix. The use of DPM2+ + + 2MSDE is strongly recommended for this model.

Also, since the use of Hires.Fix will cause the drawing to fade, two-stage generation (t2i to i2i) is recommended when creating high-resolution illustrations.

items.name: Searge-SDXL: EVOLVED v4.1 - Optimized Workflow for ComfyUI - 2023-09-05 - txt2img, img2img, inpaint, revision, controlnet, loras, ...
items.description:
Searge-SDXL: EVOLVED v4.1

Version 4.x is here.

I made a convenient install script that can install the extension and workflow, the python dependencies, and it also offer the option to download the required models.

Please read the install instructions in the readme file for more information about the install script and how to use it.

Description

Some custom nodes for ComfyUI and an easy to use SDXL 1.0 workflow. A detailed description can be found on the project repository site, here: Github Link

Installing

Detailed install instruction can be found here: Link to the readme file on Github

Usage Notes

The workflow is in the workflow folder, please load it from the JSON files to make sure you are using the latest versions of it.

The images in the examples folder have workflows embedded.

How to use this workflow

Here is an amazing Youtube video that Nerdy Rodent made about version 3.4 of the workflow. Many things have changed in v4.0 but the basics still apply. And while you are watching it, don't forget to subscribe to the channel.

Link to the Nerdy Rodent video

Updates

What's new in v4.1?

This update contains bug fixes that address issues found after v4.0 was released.

Bug Fixes

  • The high resolution latent detailer was not properly set up in the processing pipeline and did nothing

  • The debug printer node was broken - I didn't notice that because it was not connected in any of the v4.0 workflows

  • A bug related to generating with batch sizes larger than 1 has been fixed, it's now working properly

Other Changes

  • The images in the examples folder have been updated to embed the v4.1 workflow

What's new in v4.0?

  • A complete re-write of the custom node extension and the SDXL workflow

  • Highly optimized processing pipeline, now up to 20% faster than in older workflow versions

  • Support for Controlnet and Revision, up to 5 can be applied together

  • Multi-LoRA support with up to 5 LoRA's at once

  • Better Image Quality in many cases, some improvements to the SDXL sampler were made that can produce images
    with higher quality

  • Improved High Resolution modes that replace the old "Hi-Res Fix" and should generate better images

  • ... many more things, too many to mention them all here

  • Minor tweaks and fixes and the beginnings of some code restructuring, nothing user should notice in the workflows

  • Preparations for more upcoming improvements in a compatible way

  • Added compatibility with v1.x workflows, these have been used in some tutorials and did not work anymore with newer versions of the extension

  • (backwards compatibility with v2.x and older v3.x version - before v3.3 - is unfortunately not possible)

modelVersions.name: v3.2
modelVersions.description:
What's new in v3.2?

  • More prompting modes, including the "3-prompt" style that's common in other workflows (using separate prompts for the 2 CLIP models in SDXL (CLIP G & CLIP L)and a negative prompt)

    • 3-Prompt G+L-N - Similar to simple mode, but cares about a main, a secondary, and a negative prompt
      and ignores the additional style prompting fields, this is great to get similar results as on other
      workflows and makes it easier to compare the images

    • Subject - Style - The subject focused positives with the style focused negatives

    • Style - Subject - The style focused positives with the subject focused negatives

    • Style Only - Only the positive and negative style prompts are used and main/secondary/negative are ignored

    • Weighted - Overlay - The positive prompts are weighted and the negative prompts are overlaid

    • Overlay - Weighted - The positive prompts are overlaid and the negative prompts are weighted

  • Better bug fix for the "exploding" the search box issue, should finally be fixed (for real) now

  • Some additional node types to make it easier to still use my nodes in other custom workflows

  • The custom node extension should now also work on Python 3.9 again, it required 3.10 before

items.name: Wildcards for magic (and others) phenomena, colors, movements, shapes
items.description:
note: The content of these wildcards is now part of magical character and billions of characters. You'll need both to work the same way, because they share some files.

note: I made a stand-alone YAML for magic, since people still download the magic wildcards. With the YAML-format you get a single file instead of 100.

note: Yaml files will throw isseus when using: "a1111-sd-webui-tagcomplete"extension. That's related to the extension, not the wildcards.

Don't forget to leave a ❤️ to get a notification for future updates. ⭐ reviews are appreciated, too. Let me see what you created with this tool. ;)

Usage

Unleash the full power: 

Activate: Dynamic Prompts->Advanced Options->Unlink seed from prompt

Usage is pretty much the same as for "regular" wildcards.

You need the SD Dynamic Prompt Extension. Put the files into the ~\stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards Folder. They show up as a menu on the left in the Wildcards tab.

The YAML is structured and indented (that's how they work). Just with a little difference. You have to add the category layers in the wildcard.

Since this model focuses only on magic use:

__magic/magic__

You can use the subcategories for other purposes, too. (full list at the bottom)

Einstein

"The most beautiful thing we can experience is the mysterious. It is the source of all true art and science. He to whom the emotion is a stranger, who can no longer pause to wonder and stand wrapped in awe, is as good as dead —his eyes are closed. The insight into the mystery of life, coupled though it be with fear, has also given rise to religion. To know what is impenetrable to us really exists, manifesting itself as the highest wisdom and the most radiant beauty, which our dull faculties can comprehend only in their most primitive forms—this knowledge, this feeling is at the center of true religiousness. In this sense, and in this sense only, I belong in the ranks of devoutly religious men."

  • Einstein

Have you discovered some Einsteins in your creations? Leave them as review.

You are welcome

Leave a star review, if you like it. so other can find those awesome cards more easily.

I plan to add more themes as extensions in the future. SDXL is coming, and wildcards are limitless.

If you want to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. ;)

Have experimenting with it.

Content

magic:
    magic:
    words:
        adjectives:
        substantives:
        verbs:
    properties:            
        colors:
            common:
            fashion:
            special:
        patterns:
            2Dshapes:
            3Dshapes:
            lines:
    phenomena:
        natural:
        abstract:
    matter:
        state:
        movement1:
        movement2:

items.description:
Mikayla Demaiter is a social media personality, Onlyfans model, and former hockey goalkeeper, with around 2.5M followers on Instagram.

140-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (m1kayladem:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Billions of Charaters Extension - magical characters, magical attires, professions, magic types, beings
items.description:
IMPORTANT: This is an extension for the base wildcards of Billions of Characters.

I revised the wildcards to use a YAML-file now. :D Instead of 100 files you get 1 file with all the possibilties and I can maintain it more easily. I'll add a section to my guide.

There are some new features, too. (check the verson info)

Don't forget to leave a ❤️ to get a notification for future updates. ⭐ reviews are appreciated, too. Let me see what you created with this tool. ;)

note: Yaml files will throw isseus when using: "a1111-sd-webui-tagcomplete"extension. That's related to the extension, not the wildcards.

Usage

Unleash the full power: 

Activate: Dynamic Prompts->Advanced Options->Unlink seed from prompt

Usage is pretty much the same as for "regular" wildcards.

You need the SD Dynamic Prompt Extension. Put the files directly into the wildcard folder:

~\stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards

They show up as a menu on the left in the Wildcards tab.

The YAML is structured and indented (that's how they work). Just with a little difference. You have to add the category layers in the wildcard.

Example for a female character:

__BoCharsMag/female/modern__

A cool thing you can do, too, is using a wildcard "*" in the wildcards. So you could use the normal chararcter wildcards in the same prompt and get chars from both sets:

__BoChars*/female/modern__
__clothings*__ # for clothings from both sets

I made easy to use wildcards for character creations.

There are some wildcards that are not used for it. Have a look what's in there, too. You'll find a full list below. You can use each subcategory separately.

You are welcome

Leave a star review, if you like it. so other can find those awesome cards more easily.

I plan to add more themes as extensions in the future. SDXL is coming, and wildcards are limitless.

If you want to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. ;)

Have experimenting with it.

  • 2 character prompts for classic chars:

    • magical_male_person_classic

    • magical_female_person_classic

  • 2 versions of random character generation

    • magical_gender_rnd

    • magical_gender_rnd_classic

  • magical lightings

  • magical words (whatever you want to do with them, I use them for "magical properties")
